-- CTC Media Audience Share Falls to Lowest in Five Weeks, TNS Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-03-12T18:42:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/ctc-media-audience-share-falls-to-lowest-in-five-weeks-tns-says.html
CTC Media (CTCM)  Inc.’s average daily
share of television viewers fell to 7.6 percent in the seven
days to March 4, the lowest in five weeks, according to data
compiled by TNS-Global.  CTC’s TV channel , the U.S.-traded company’s biggest source
of advertising revenue, remained the fourth-largest in Russia in
the week to March 4, data researcher TNS-Global said in an e-
mail today. CTC’s audience share was down from 8 percent in the
previous week and the lowest since the period ended Jan. 29,
when it fell to 7.5 percent,  TNS-Global data showed .  NTV Television  maintained the biggest average daily
audience share, TNS data showed. NTV’s audience expanded to 16.1
percent in the week to March 4, from 14.3 percent a week
earlier, while  Russia ’s  Pervyi Kanal , which is controlled by the
government, had 15.6 percent, compared with 13.8 percent in the
previous period.  Rossiya-1 Television, also controlled by the government,
remained the country’s third-biggest channel by audience in the
week with a 12.4 percent share, down from 13.7 percent, the data
showed.  TNS-Global monitors television viewers ages four years and
older in Russian towns of at least 100,000 people.  Shares of CTC fell 0.1 percent to $10.96 at 2:34 p.m. in
